The first chunk for your media track must have a timestamp of 0 (received ${t}). Non-zero first timestamps are often caused by directly piping frames or audio data from a MediaStreamTrack into the encoder. Their timestamps are typically relative to the age of the document, which is probably what you want.

If you want to offset all timestamps of a track such that the first one is zero, set firstTimestampBehavior: 'offset' in the options.
